FIRST INFORMATION REPORT APPLICATION
(under the Cyber Crime Prevention, Investigation, and Trial Rules, 2021 and the Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 § 154)

To: The Station House Officer (SHO)
{LOCAL_POLICE_STATION}
District {PLACE}

Subject: Online Financial Fraud / Wrong UPI Transfer of Rs. {AMOUNT} — Victim: {USER_NAME}, VPA {VPA} → {VPA_PAYEE}, UTR {UTR}, {TXN_DATE}

Sir,

1. I, {USER_NAME}, resident of {ADDRESS} (mobile {MOBILE_NO}; email {EMAIL}; Aadhaar **********), hereby lodge this First Information Report under Section 154 of the Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 read with Section 66-D of the Information Technology Act, 2000 and Section 318 read with Sections 319, 336(3), 338 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.

2. The facts giving rise to the present FIR are:
   (i) On {TXN_DATE} (UTR {UTR}) I made a UPI debit of Rs. {AMOUNT} from VPA {VPA}. The credit was to VPA {VPA_PAYEE}, account number {BENEFICIARY_ACCOUNT_NO} (IFSC {BENEFICIARY_IFSC}) held with {BENEFICIARY_BANK}.
   (ii) I had been deceived by messages (chat record attached) purportedly from a known merchant offering a job/interview/auction/family-emergency, against which I confirmed.
   (iii) The amounts are above the threshold of Rs. Ten Lakh (1 000 000) — this FIR is therefore lodged in strict compliance with the Cyber Crime Prevention, Investigation and Trial Rules, 2021, which mandate institution of cognisable offences within 24 hours of complaint and registration of FIR if the investigation does not yield a closure report within 15 working days.

3. Documents annexed:
   (i) UPI transaction slip (UTR {UTR});
   (ii) Chat / SMS / WhatsApp screenshots;
   (iii) Bank account statement showing the debit;
   (iv) KYC documents of the impersonator if any;
   (v) My Aadhaar copy.

4. Prayer:
   (a) Registration of FIR under BNSS 154;
   (b) Freezing of beneficiary account under 102 CrPC read with the IT Act (now BNNS 2023);
   (c) Issue of Look-Out Circular against the beneficiary and, where identified, the syndicate;
   (d) Issuance of directions to {BENEFICIARY_BANK} for match-action under RBI Circular DBOD.No.Leg.BC.74/09.07.005/2013-14 (Customer Protection Circular).

5. I hereby declare that the facts above are true to my knowledge and belief, and that no part of my claim is false, frivolous or vexatious.

6. I request the investigating officer to coordinate with the Head of the Cyber-Crime Bureau at the District Police Office, {PLACE}.

Place: {PLACE}
Date: {TODAY_DATE}

Complainant
{USER_NAME}

Verification: I, {USER_NAME}, do hereby declare that the above particulars are true to my knowledge and belief.

Witnesses:
1. __________________________ Address: __________________________
2. __________________________ Address: __________________________

